data.description: Charming partial brick covered porch front bungalow with finished basement on lovely lot in Kenwood! Lovingly maintained gardens frame the home and provide instant curb appeal. Enter tiled foyer and into spacious living/family room flooded with natural light from 3 large front-facing windows. Side window features plantation shutters. An arched throughway leads to the separate dining room accented by chair rail and a chandelier to sit over the table space. Convenient welcome closet exists in this space. Kitchen off of dining room is situated in the rear of the home boasting beautiful white washed cabinets, blue tops, almond appliances, a ceiling fan, and a perfectly placed window over the sink. Side entrance door exists. First floor primary bedroom is situated in the front of the home with ceiling fan, double window and side window, and a large double closet. 2nd bedroom on the main is situated in the rear of the home with 2 windows, a ceiling fan, and a nice closet. Full hall bath is accented by crown molding and features black and white tiled floor and pristine white tile around the tub/shower combo. The upper level includes 2 generously sized bedrooms each with windows and closets. Attic eaves offer ample storage space! The large basement runs for the full length of the house offering a family room for stretching out, partial windows for light, a utility and laundry room, storage under the stairs, and walk up to rear yard.  Vented glass block windows exist in family room and storage area. The beautiful level yard is fully fenced featuring a patio with sun shelter, perfect for relaxing, mature trees for shade and lovely gardens. NEW Thompson Creek spouts with covers. Battery back up sump pump! This beautiful home shows pride of long-time ownership at every turn! A true MUST see! Hurry up and schedule your private tour TODAY! **Please note that the doorknobs on doors in between dining room and family room are being replaced**
